A pilot died on Tuesday morning when a plane crashed in Tom
Burke outside Lephalale. Cops say they are investigating a case of culpable homicide. Police spokesperson Colonel Moatshe Ngoepe said it is
alleged that at about 06:00, the pilot of a light aircraft departed from Genoa
farm heading to Gauteng. Ngoepe said within few minutes after his departure, the
aircraft lost control and landed with its front. The plane reportedly landed on the ground in the bushes
around Enkelfontein farm, killing the pilot instantly. The deceased was positively identified by the family, he is
allegedly from Melkbosh farm in the Tom Burke ouside Lephalale. The cause of this accident is still unknown at this stage. Ngoepe said the investigations by both the South African
Police Service and the Civil Aviation Authority are still underway.